For those of you who are using Spring Boot, that project is already bundling all the SLF4J dependencies, meaning listing them directly in your Maven project will not work since there will be different versions of your logging packages if you do that.

Spring Boot ships with Logback and log4j support, where Logback is the one which is enabled by default. So if you want to use log4j for logging, the only dependencies you need for that are the following:

```
    &lt;!-- This is the latest version at the time of writing --&gt;
	&lt;dependency&gt;
	    &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
	    &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
	    &lt;version&gt;3.1.3&lt;/version&gt;
	    &lt;exclusions&gt;
            &lt;exclusion&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-logging&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;/exclusion&gt;
      &lt;/exclusions&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... other dependencies ... --&gt;
	&lt;dependency&gt;
	    &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
	    &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-log4j2&lt;/artifactId&gt;
	    &lt;version&gt;3.1.3&lt;/version&gt;
	&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

If you want to use Logback instead of log4j you have to remove the `spring-boot-starter-log4j2` dependency and also delete the `spring-boot-starter-logging` exclusion.

